<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910517-0179</DOCNO><DOCID>910517-0179.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- USX Corp.:   Selling Program Is Set Up   For Odd-Lot Shareholders</HL><DATE>05/17/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   X</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)</IN><NS>STOCK andamp; OTHER MARKET NEWS (STK)</NS><RE>PENNSYLVANIA (PA)</RE><LP>   USX Corp. said it established a voluntary, commission-freeselling program for shareholders who, as a result of therecently approved stock restructuring, will receive 99 orfewer shares of USX-U.S. Steel Group common shares. Theprogram allows shareholders to sell all of their eligibleshares without paying a brokerage commission, the Pittsburghcompany said.   Shares submitted by participating shareholders will besold on their behalf by a New York Stock Exchange member firmand will not be purchased by USX. The price paid per sharewill be the weighted average selling price for all sharessubmitted from May 15 to June 24, and sold periodicallythrough the program.</LP><TEXT>   The information agent for the selling program isShareholder Communications Corp. The program will expire onJune 24 unless extended by USX.</TEXT></DOC>